1. 	The "P" in HTTP means protocol. Explain in your own words what a protocol is. \
\cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \
According to MDN, a protocol is a set of rules and regulations that define how data is \'93exchanged within or between computers\'94 [MDN, 2023]. It contains specifications of format to make it possible for both computers to communicate effectively.\
\
\
\pard\tx566\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 2.   	 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
HTTP is built on top of which protocol? \cb1 \uc0\u8232  HTTP is built on top of TCP, \'93a TLS-encrypted connection\'94 [MDN, 2023]. It is a type of transport-layer protocol, namely the Transmission Control Protocol. The important characteristics of TCP are that a connection between the client and server are established before transmission of data commences. The data is also sent in the same order it was received in, and \'93is sent without errors or duplication\'94. [IMBm 2021]. The amount of data handled is scalable and only restricted by what the server itself can handle. [MDN, 2023]\
\
\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 3.   	\cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
If a request is successful, what will the status code of the response be? \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \
If a request is successful, the status code could be any 2xx code, depending on the specifics needing to be relayed to the client. A plain 200 code will relay that the request was received and processed according to the HTTP method used. A 201 or 204 status code would convey slightly more information. A 201 code, for example, would provide more information in the status, relaying that the POST or PUT method used in the request was successfully handled and a new resource has been created.[MDN, 2023]. A 204 status, for example, would detail that the request has been handles successfully, but that no resource has been sent to the client. This is helpful to reassure a client that all is as it should be, in case they were expecting some content to be returned through their request.\
\pard\tx566\pardeftab720\sl360\slmult1\partightenfactor0
