\cf2 \cb3 7. 	Which status message can you expect if a server does not allow you permission to request a specific resource? \cb1 \uc0\u8232 If you do not have permissions to request a specific resource, the server will return a 401 \'93Unauthorised\'94 or 403 \'93Forbidden\'94 status message. If you need to be logged in or have some sort of authorisation token that you did not submit with your HTTP request, the server will return the 401 status message to convey that it needs some sort of authentication of the user issuing the request. If the user is logged in, however, and is trying to access material beyond what s/he is permitted to (say, trying to change or grant something that only an admin of a website has the permissions for), then the status 403 will be issued, to explain to the user that they do not have permission to request that specific resource. [Webdevsimplified, 2020] [MDN, 2023]\u8232 \
